Get the hint yet?  Spells in general have limited uses.  Learn what those limits are and you'll be more powerful then the clown next to you who hasn't learned it yet.  <br>
<br>
I'm not for zonewide removal of CoTH because a few found a way to use the spell that the DEVs hadn't either thought of or intended.  This all goes back to Testing. Players do not seem to understand that SOE uses test server for one purpose. That is to see if the code will cause damage to their equipment or cause catastrophic memory failures. Then when they know it won't do that They put it on regular servers(via the patches) and let the rest of the EQ playerbase to finalize their BETA testing.  Once they get that done they start 'fixing' things they find because now there are 400k people testing it and not just 400.<br>
<br>
The way to fix PoN Maze coh'ing was to make the maze a zone in of its self and disabling coh there, thus keeping coh in PoN and not allowing people to be coh'd into the maze after it was done.<br>
<br>
For those who think coh is just a waste of spellbook space then all I have to say is delete it from you book and go on about your lives.<br>
<br>
About Acrylia and summoning of a hero. I personally think this was a neat twist on the failure of a spell.<br>
